page.title: 19Farnborough,Bromley,S.E.
page.content: Farnborough is a small village.It is bounded by the A21 to the North,and Green Belt land to the south.It has one main street.The shops were built in 1910. The oldest part of Farnborough is around the triangle in Church Road.The houses here are 200-400 years old. There is an antique shop and a violin shop where the old village shops used to be. The first big development was in 1907 when the roads named after saints were built.More houses are being built all the time. There are two pubs,the Woodman and the Change of Horses.The George used to be a pub but it is now a restaurant. There is a laundry,a small electronics firm,a telephone exchange and a research centre.
